### Mozic backend — Supabase HTTP collection
### Works with IntelliJ's built-in HTTP Client, or the VS Code "REST Client" extension.
### Run the login request first, copy `access_token` from the response into @token below.

@baseUrl = https://ktwzmigxumrpblamerzw.supabase.co
@apikey = REPLACE_WITH_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
@token = REPLACE_ME_AFTER_LOGIN

### Login (demo account — see README.md for the full list; login is by email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/v1/token?grant_type=password
apikey: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@mozic.dev",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Songs — newest first (default catalog order)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/songs?select=*&order=created_at.desc&limit=20
apikey: {{apikey}}

### Songs — most popular, page 2 (Range-header pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/songs?select=*&order=popularity.desc
apikey: {{apikey}}
Range: 10-19
Prefer: count=exact

### Song by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/songs?id=eq.song-1&select=*
apikey: {{apikey}}

### Search — everything matching "echo"
POST {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/rpc/search_catalog
apikey: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "q": "echo"
}

### Search — songs only
POST {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/rpc/search_catalog
apikey: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "q": "night",
  "result_type": "song"
}

### Playlists — world category
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/playlists?category=eq.WORLD&select=*
apikey: {{apikey}}

### Songs in a playlist (joined via embedding)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/playlist_songs?playlist_id=eq.playlist-1&select=position,songs(*)&order=position
apikey: {{apikey}}

### Profile by id (public read, no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/profiles?id=eq.<uuid>&select=*
apikey: {{apikey}}

### A user's public playlists
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/playlists?owner_id=eq.<uuid>&is_public=eq.true&select=*
apikey: {{apikey}}

### Follow a user (auth required — follower_id must equal the caller)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/follows
apikey: {{apikey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "follower_id": "<your-uuid>",
  "followee_id": "<their-uuid>"
}

### Unfollow (auth required)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/follows?follower_id=eq.<your-uuid>&followee_id=eq.<their-uuid>
apikey: {{apikey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Conversations for the logged-in user (auth required — RLS scopes to participant rows)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/conversations?select=*
apikey: {{apikey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Messages in a conversation, most recent first (auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/messages?conversation_id=eq.conv-1&select=*&order=sent_at.desc
apikey: {{apikey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
